               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; incipits and headings of the texts; short postscripts to the Gospels of Matthew and Mark; chapter numbers (in the “tituli”), titles and the word mǝʿǝraf; elements of the punctuation signs and Ethiopic numbers.&#xD;
On the incipit page of each Gospel, a few lines are rubricated (in groups of two lines, alternating with black lines).</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- The “tituli” are numbered only when they precede the Gospel text; within the text itself the chapters are not numbered. The number of the “tituli” for the Gospel of Mark (47) is given erroneously.</note>
                     <note>- The introduction to the Four Gospels is missing.</note>
                     <note>- The canon tables are missing.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
