                           <locus target="#111vb" n="#2">Fol. 111vb, l.2</locus>. Blessing for the persons mentioned.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 111vb, l.2: ወከማሁ፡ ይባርኮ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ለገብሩ፡ አቡነ፡ አስተአ፡ ድንግል፡ ወአቡሁ፡ አቡነ፡ አሥራተ</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 111vb: And likewise may God bless His servant ʾabunä ʾAstäʾa Dǝngǝl and his father ʾabunä ʾAśratä …</q>
                           Written as continuation and part of the preceding Gospel text.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#137ra">Fol. 137ra</locus>-rb. Record concerning a reconciliation agreement and punishment for its transgressors (?).<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in difficult language, a mixture of Amharic and Gǝʿǝz. The reconciliation took place on Mäskäräm 21, 1889 E.C. (September 30, 1896 A.D.). The note was written down on Ṭǝqǝmt 1 (October 10).
The note mentions ras Mängäša (Yoḥannǝs, d. 1906 A.D.), governor of Tǝgray in 1889-1906, as well as a number of geographical locations, including Mǝʾsar Gwǝhila and ʿAddiqäḥarsi.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Fol. 2r. Note: መጽሐፈ፡ ሕንኪ፡ አለሽ፡ በወርሐ፡ መጋቢት፡ ተጽሕፈት፨&#xD;
- Fols. 78r, 78v, 79r, 79v, etc. Marginal notes repeating chapter titles.&#xD;
- Fols. 92r, 95v, in the upper margin. Corrections in red (?).&#xD;
- Fols. 136v, 137r, in the bottom margin. Pen trials.</item>
                     </list>
